<topic id="ofb-configuring-openai-connection">
    <title>Configuring <ph><tm tmtype="tm">OpenAI</tm></ph> Connection</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <keyword outputclass="label">Site Configuration</keyword>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <body>
    <p>The semantic search functionality requires that you configure <ph keyref="product"/> to
      connect to <tm tmtype="tm">OpenAI</tm> on your behalf. </p>
    <p>In the <xref href="ofb-organization-profile-page.dita"><i>Organization Profile</i>
        page</xref>, you must configure an API key obtained from <tm tmtype="tm">OpenAI</tm> to
      allow <ph keyref="product"/> to connect to their API. </p>
    <p>
      <note id="note_uxg_jpq_dzb">Make sure that the key is specifically generated to be used only
        in <ph keyref="product"/>.</note>
    </p>
    <p>Additionally, you can specify an optional <tm tmtype="tm">OpenAI</tm> organization that will
      be used to track usage.</p>
    <p>
      <fig id="fig_gwd_h5q_dzb">
        <title>Configure OpenAI Connection Details</title>
        <image href="../img/ofb-configuring-openai-connection.png" id="image_b4r_wpq_dzb"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <section id="section_bdv_mfv_dzb">
      <title>Generating an <tm tmtype="tm">OpenAI</tm> API Key</title>
      <p>You can generate a new secret API Key in the <xref
          href="https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys" format="html" scope="external">API
          keys</xref> page from your <tm tmtype="tm">OpenAI</tm> user account.</p>
    </section>
    </body>
